content:
Here is the cleaned up text:

Create an Integration Procedure to handle OmniScript data.

Drag the Integration Procedure Action into the OmniScript's structure panel.

To select the Integration Procedure to be called, click in the Integration Procedure field, and select from the list. You can type in the field to filter the list.

Use the Response Transformations properties to specify the input and to trim or rename the output JSON.

Send JSON Path — Specifies the JSON node that contains the input for the Integration Procedure.

Send JSON Node — Renames the JSON node that contains the input for the Integration Procedure.

Response JSON Path — Specifies the JSON node that contains the output to return to the OmniScript.

Response JSON Node — Renames the JSON node that contains the output to return to the OmniScript.

Use the Extra Payload property to send additional key-value pairs to the Integration Procedure as input data.

Specify any additional Integration Procedure Action properties you need.

Enable the Integration Procedure's Queueable Chainable settings by clicking the Is Queueable Chainable? checkbox and adding a Key-Value pair with KEY "useQueueableApexRemoting" and VALUE "true".

Configure these properties to map the response to an element: Response JSON Node, Response JSON Path, and the name of the OmniScript Element receiving the value.

Note: When an OmniScript invokes an Integration Procedure asynchronously, the Integration Procedure continues running if the user goes to the next step, but not if the user navigates away from the OmniScript.
title: OmniStudio Integration Procedure Action
